h3. Issue Summary
The *Two Dimensional Filter Statistics* macro is a great widget we can use to pull up JIRA data within our beautiful Confluence pages. This feature is awesome to create great reports!
Lately, we have noting that this widget is not behaving well when it is inserted within a Panel macro.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Inert a *Panel* macro;
# Within the Panel, call *{two* and insert the *Two Dimensional Filter Statistics*;
# Configure it with the JIRA filter and fields you want;
# Make sure to save the widget properties and then insert it into the page;
# Publish the page.

h3. Expected Results
The *Two Dimensional Filter Statistics* results load in the page.

h3. Actual Results
A blank frame is placed in the screen.

*Notes*:
* This issue occurs intermittently. 

h3. Workaround
 # Remove the *Two Dimensional Filter Statistics* macro from the panel;
 # Directly in the page, add the *Two Dimensional Filter Statistics* macro;
 # Make sure to save the properties and then insert the macro;
 # Cut the macro and paste it into the *Panel*;
 # Publish the page.

Hello,

 

Our organizatoin needs the ability to insert in a confluence page a field value by key id

 

example:
 * Sentence in confluence page
 * "The current release status is {color:#4c9aff}IN PROGRESS {color:#172b4d}and the audience will be{color} PUBLIC{color:#172b4d}"{color}{color}

{color:#4c9aff}{color:#172b4d}We'd like to insert the fied as follow:{color}{color}
 * {color:#4c9aff}{color:#172b4d}Solution to the problem{color}{color}
 * {color:#4c9aff}{color:#172b4d}"The current release status is _*/filedToText*(KeyId=123:printFieldName="status")_ and the audience will be _*/filedToText*(KeyId=123:printFieldName="Audience")_{color}{color}

 

Without this feature confluence is pretty much *usless* for us, as you have to expect someone to manually update the text based on changes in Jira.

h3. Issue Summary

A new feature/suggestion is requested to adding a new comment to Jira issue directly from ConfluenceSteps to Reproduce.

Customer use-case involves in reviewing the Confluence documents in the meetings and updating the Jira issues eventually, a feature of updating the Jira comments is requested by customer for further flexibility.

 
{noformat}
{noformat}

h3. Issue Summary

Custom content searches using the REST API slows down as the search offset increases.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a Confluence Cloud app that introduces its own custom content type.

{noformat}
{
    "name": "Confluence Cloud Test App",
    "description": "Confluence Cloud Test App",
    "key": "k15t-confluence-cloud-test-app",
    "scopes": [
        "read",
        "write"
    ],
    "baseUrl": "https://confluence-test-app.eu.ngrok.io",
    "vendor": {
        "name": "K15t GmbH",
        "url": "http://www.k15t.com"
    },
    "authentication": {
        "type": "none"
    },
    "apiVersion": 2,
    "appVersion": "1",
    "apiMigrations": {
        "gdpr": true
    },
    "lifecycle": {},
    "modules": {
        "customContent": [
            {
                "key": "item",
                "name": {
                    "value": "Test App"
                },
                "uiSupport": {
                    "listViewComponent": {
                        "moduleKey": "test-app-list-view"
                    },
                    "contentViewComponent": {
                        "moduleKey": "test-app-list-view"
                    },
                    "icons": {
                        "item": {
                            "width": 16,
                            "height": 16,
                            "url": "/logo192.png"
                        },
                        "list": {
                            "width": 16,
                            "height": 16,
                            "url": "/logo192.png"
                        }
                    }
                },
                "apiSupport": {
                    "bodyType": "raw",
                    "supportedContainerTypes": [
                        "space",
                        "page"
                    ]
                }
            }
        ],
        "generalPages": [
            {
                "key": "test-app-list-view",
                "url": "/&spaceKey={space.key}",
                "location": "none",
                "name": {
                    "value": "Test App"
                }
            }
        ]
    }
}{noformat}
 # Create ~1000 pages in a single space. Example:

{noformat}
POST /rest/api/content

{
    "type": "page",
    "title": "Page 1",
    "space": {
        "key": "LT"
    }
}{noformat}
 # Create one custom content item underneath each of these pages. Example:

{noformat}
{
    "type": "ac:k15t-confluence-cloud-test-app:item",
    "title": "Test Item New",
    "space": {
        "key": "LT"
    },
    "container": {
        "type": "page",
        "id": "123"
    },
    "body": {
        "raw": {
            "value": {},
            "representation": "raw"
        }
    }
}{noformat}
 # Fetch all content items, 200 at a time:

{noformat}
GET /rest/api/content?type=ac:k15t-confluence-cloud-test-app:item&spaceKey=LT&start=0&limit=200
GET /rest/api/content?type=ac:k15t-confluence-cloud-test-app:item&spaceKey=LT&start=200&limit=200
GET /rest/api/content?type=ac:k15t-confluence-cloud-test-app:item&spaceKey=LT&start=400&limit=200
GET /rest/api/content?type=ac:k15t-confluence-cloud-test-app:item&spaceKey=LT&start=600&limit=200
GET /rest/api/content?type=ac:k15t-confluence-cloud-test-app:item&spaceKey=LT&start=800&limit=200{noformat}
h3. Expected Results

Each query takes takes less than a few seconds.
h3. Actual Results

The duration of each query increases such that the first request takes 2 seconds to complete. The second one 5 seconds. The third one 10 seconds. The fourth one 16 seconds. The fifth one 25 seconds.

This means, each pagination request gets slower and slower. Fetching all 1000 custom content items takes *58 seconds* in sum. Adding some expands, like we do in our app, worsens the performance even more.
h3. Workaround

None
